-- Ravens’ Ray Lewis Tells Teammates He’ll Retire After Playoffs
-- B y   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n
-- 2013-01-02T17:22:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-02/ravens-ray-lewis-tells-teammates-he-ll-retire-after-playoffs.html
Baltimore Ravens linebacker  Ray Lewis 
told his teammates he’ll retire after the postseason.  The former National Football League defensive player of the
year said today that “this will be my last ride,” according to
comments posted by the team on Twitter and on NFL.com.  Lewis has been out since mid-October with a torn triceps.
The Ravens are scheduled to play the Indianapolis Colts in the
first round of the playoffs this weekend  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
